<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/057d7c021856b9f09b39a50d5676a153.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 3 and c = 7. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.3</li><li>25.4</li><li>64.6</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{49}={9}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{49}-{9}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{40}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{40}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.3245553203368}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.3}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{25.376933525125}\approx{25.4}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{64.623066474875}\approx{64.6}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>